
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    ${ include('../bolt/templates/head.literal', './package.json') }

    <script title="debug">
        window.DEBUG = true;
    </script>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../bolt/module.css">
    ${ include('../bolt/templates/style.html') }

    <style>
    rotary-input {
        max-width: 10rem;
    }

    * + rotary-input,
    * + xy-input {
        margin-top: 2rem;
    }

    .link-button {
        --height: 2.5rem;
        --border-width: 1px;

        border-color: currentcolor;
        border-radius: 0.3125rem;
    }

    .link-button:hover {
        color: #4f6473;
    }

    * + .link-button {
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }
    </style>

    ${ include('./xy-input/templates/xy-input-shadow.html') }
</head>

<body class="docs-grid grid 3x-grid @1-6x-grid @2-9x-grid" style="align-content: start;">
    <header class="x1 3x @1-x3 @1-4x @2-x4">
        <h1>Form elements</h1>
        <p>A collection of advanced form controls published as custom elements.
        Ranges of these elements can be scaled with linear, logarithm, or
        exponential curves, values and tickmarks can by expressed in dB, Hz,
        seconds and other units, and the elements may be used in forms with their
        values being submitted like other form controls.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="x1 3x @1-x3 @1-4x @2-x4">
        <h2>&lt;range-input&gt;</h2>
        <p>A horizontal slider with an <code>&lt;input type="range"&lt;</code>
        at its core, clickable tick marks, and a live value readout.</p>
        <a class="link-button button" href="./range-input/">Documentation</a>
    </div>

    <range-input class="x1 y2 3x" name="scale" min="-1" max="1" ticks="-1 -0.8 -0.6 -0.4 -0.2 0 0.2 0.4 0.6 0.8 1" value="0">Scale</range-input>

    <div class="x1 3x @1-x3 @1-4x @2-x4">
        <h2>&lt;rotary-input&gt;</h2>
        <p>A rotating knob that can be dragged vertically, with clickable tick
        marks and live value readout.</p>
        <a class="link-button button" href="./rotary-input/">Documentation</a>
    </div>

    <rotary-input class="x2 2x y3" name="pan" min="-1" max="1" ticks="-1 -0.8 -0.6 -0.4 -0.2 0 0.2 0.4 0.6 0.8 1">Pan</rotary-input>

    <div class="x1 3x @1-x3 @1-4x @2-x4">
        <h2>&lt;xy-input&gt;</h2>
        <p>An input that contains a series of one or more x/y handles and an
        (optional) background plot. Both axes may be scaled, and the element has
        a <code>value</code> property that returns an array of coordinates.</p>
        <a class="link-button button" href="./xy-input/">Documentation</a>
    </div>

    <xy-input class="x1 y4 3x">Envelope</xy-input>

    ${ include('../bolt/templates/scripts.html') }

    <script type="module">
        import RangeInput  from './range-input.js';
        import RotaryInput from './rotary-input.js';
        import XYInput     from './xy-input.js';
    </script>
</body>
